{{setTitle "React Helpers for Internationalization"}}

<h1>React Helpers for Internationalization</h1>

<p>
    If you're using <a href="http://facebook.github.io/react/">Facebook's React</a>, the React Intl Mixin are an easy way to internationalize your templates.
</p>

<p>This module clocks in at {{helperSize}} minified and compressed. This includes both the React Intl mixin and the IntlMessageFormat polyfill with data for many languages.</p>

{{sectionHeading "Installation"}}

<p>
    You can install {{code "react-intl"}} through <a href="http://bower.io">Bower</a> on the client side.
</p>

{{#code "shell"}}
$ bower install react-intl
{{/code}}

<p>
    Alternatively, you can install via <a href="http://npmjs.org">npm</a> on the server.
</p>

{{#code "shell"}}
$ npm install react-intl
{{/code}}

<aside>
    <p>
        <strong>Note:</strong> When working with the client-side version of this helper, make sure that {{code "window.Intl"}} is
        available, otherwise you'll need to install a polyfill. For more information check out the <a href="/quickstart/browser#browser-compatibility">browser compatibility chart</a>.
    </p>
</aside>

<p>
    The browser distribution is bundled with <a href="https://github.com/yahoo/intl-messageformat">IntlMessageFormat</a>. You need to make sure that both React and the Intl polyfill are loaded before {{code "react-intl"}}.
</p>

{{#code "html"}}
<script src="path/to/react.js"></script>
<script src="path/to/bower_components/react-intl/dist/react-intl.min.js"></script>
{{/code}}

